<p class="title">Chapter 7: Hymn 42: Become a Flower (No.07)</p>
<p class="para">"<i>Alert: I thought I told you to be careful when<br>performing pipework.</i>" Pod scolds me as she bandages<br>my hand.<br><br>I scalded myself while I was inspecting the base—I came into<br>contact with some of the steam going through the pipes.<br><br>"<i>Gratitude: But I'm very proud of you for working so hard<br>despite being reassigned here for poor behavior.</i>"<br><br>My enthusiasm delights her. I puff up my cheeks.<br>I mean, this base bores the heck out of me. It's not like<br>there's much to do here <i>besides</i> work.<br><br>"<i>Alert: However! You must always remain diligent and<br>focused when working!</i>"<br><br>"Ugh, yeah, I <i>know</i>. I'll be fine. And—"<br><br><i>You're so old fashioned for bandaging an android</i>,<br>I think, but decide to keep to myself. Pod probably knows<br>that already, so whatever. At least I'll be able to skip out on<br>working for a bit. If I'm going to be bored either way, I guess<br>I'd rather be doing nothing at all. So, in that case...sure, might<br>as well just take the bandage. I'll think of it as a placebo.</p>
