<p class="title">Chapter 8: Diary Found in an Empty Room (No.08)</p>
<p class="para">Red chassis Pods draw nearer, their red lights glinting<br>menacingly. I'm at the end of my rope. I run through the<br>halls of the lunar base. The other girls have lost their<br>minds and control—I evade them.<br><br>"<i>Report: 10H... D... Do... Do n0t run fRom h0me...</i>"<br><br>"Shut up! You sound like a broken radio!"<br><br>I ward off the Pods' attacks, and I throw a fist into one<br>with all my might.<br><br>"<i>Report: Report: Rep0rt: REp0Rt:<br>RRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRR</i>"<br><br>On the far side of the airlock, I grab the handle to the<br>door leading to the outside of the base. The handle is hot—<br>a clear indication that passing this threshold is off-limits—<br>and my hand stings as it burns.<br><br>"For crying out loud, what <i>is</i> this, Pod!?"<br><br>The girl who bandaged me is gone now.<br>But I can't let grief weigh me down.<br>I have to get out of here.<br>For humanity's sake.<br>For...the promise I made with Pod.</p>
